column1: #Text=Khan Bahadur Bakhshi Ghulam Haider Khan

#Text=( died 1828 AD ) was Faujdar of a unit at the time of Battle of Assaye , which was a major battle of the Second Anglo-Maratha War under the command of Major General Arthur Wellesley ( Duke of Wellington ) .
#Text=Latterly , he became the royal chief head of the military services hence called the Mir Bakhshi .
#Text=He was in charge of intelligence gathering , and also made recommendations to the royal court for military appointments and promotions .
#Text=Services
#Text=Khan Bahadur Bakshi Ghulam Haider Khan was first employed with Nizam of Hyderabad .
#Text=He then joined army and became Faujdar .
#Text=He fought in the Battle of Assaye , which was a major battle of the Second Anglo-Maratha War under the command of Major General Arthur Wellesley ( Duke of Wellington ) .
#Text=Because of his services in the army under the command of ( Duke of Wellington ) , he was awarded the title ‘ Khan Bahadur ’ and a land of 1400 Bigha at Rewari .
#Text=He was latterly employed with Appa Sahib alias Mudhoji II Bhonsle .

#Text=In 1817 , he vehemently opposed the action of Appa Sahib when he was conspiring against British forces ; as a result Appa Sahib was deposed and forwarded to Allahabad in custody , while Khan Bahadur Bakshi Ghulam Haider Khan was placed as ‘ Kamidan ’ , a commandant in the army .
#Text=He remained on this post for 12 years .
#Text=Family history
#Text=His ancestor ‘ Shaikh Umaruddin ’ came to India along with the caravan of Sultan Shahabuddin Muhammad Ghori and settled at Sultanpur , near the River Sutlej and River Bayas .
#Text=His sons went to Delhi and deputed as Mufti at Rewari .
#Text=This profession remained in their family for centuries .
#Text=Khan Bahadur Bakshi Ghulam Haider Khan was the son of Mufti Noorul Haq ibn Amanul Haq . [ 1 ]
#Text=Brothers
#Text=He had three brothers : Ghulam Hussain , Amanul Haq , and Mohibul Haq .
#Text=Mohibul Haq was the judge at Nagpur state .
#Text=Amanul Haq during the reign of Akbar Shah II ( King of Delhi ) took service with Raghoji II Bhonsle ( Raja of Nagpur ) and served him for many years .
#Text=He had eight sons : Shamsul Haq , Sanaul Haq , Zafar Ali Khan , Abdul Ali Khan , Imdad Hussain , Ghulam Yahya , Fazlul Haq and Ahsanul Haq .
#Text=Zafar Ali Khan was the Subahdar for nine years at Nagpur and received 6000 rupees annually as salary .
#Text=After his death , his all five sons got pensions .
#Text=His one son , Inayat Ali Khan received pension of rupees 600 against the services in army and for the same reason , he remained Honorary Magistrate at Rewari , District Gurgaon .
#Text=The second son of Amanul Haq , Abdul Ali Khan was Risaldar in one of the Punjab regimentduring 1857 War of Independence .
#Text=The son of Sanaul Haq , Mohib Hussain Khan became Subahdar of Bhandara , near Nagpur . [ 2 ] In 1853 , when Britishers took over Nagpur , he was appointed as Extra-Assistant Commissioner .
#Text=He died in 1870 .
#Text=His son Nooruddin Hussain Khan was Risaldar at Nagpur for many years and another son , Moizuddin Hussain Khan was employed at Nizam of Hyderabad .
#Text=Children
#Text=He had four sons : Ghulam Mohamamd Khan , Khairat Ali Khan , Jeevan Ali Khan and Auz Ali Khan .
#Text=Three of his sons were employed in the army of the States of Nagpur .
#Text=After his death , his elder son Ghulam Mohamad Khan ( died 1833 AD ) latterly became the ‘ Kamidan ’ in his place .
#Text=Sardar Bahadur Tafazzul Hussain Khan
#Text=was the son of Ghulam Mohamad Khan .
